-- Nomura appoints Todd Sandoz new equity trading head
-- 
-- Fri Jan 10, 2014 04:30AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 10 (Reuters) - Japanese investment bank Nomura <8604.t> said on Friday it had appointed Todd Sandoz as global head of execution services and equity trading.

Sandoz joins from Credit Suisse <CSGN.VX>, where he spent 17 years and was most recently head of global foreign exchange and short-term interest rates trading in London.